  "prompt": "How was Ankara chosen to be the capital of Turkey?",
  "response": "Ankara was chosen as the capital of Turkey in 1923 by Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk, the founder and first President of the Republic of Turkey. The decision was influenced by several factors:\n\n1. **Strategic Location**: Ankara is located in the center of the country, making it a more defensible position compared to Istanbul, which is on the western edge and more vulnerable to foreign threats.\n\n2. **Historical Significance**: Ankara has a long history dating back to the Hittite Empire and was an important city during the Roman and Byzantine periods. This historical significance added to its appeal as a national capital.\n\n3. **Symbol of the New Republic**: Moving the capital from Istanbul, which had been the seat of the Ottoman Empire, to Ankara symbolized a break from the old imperial system and the establishment of a new, modern republic.\n\n4. **Role in the War of Independence**: Ankara served as the headquarters for the Turkish National Movement during the Turkish War of Independence (1919-1923). This role cemented its importance in the eyes of the new republic's leaders.\n\nOn October 13, 1923, the Turkish Grand National Assembly officially declared Ankara as the new capital. This decision was a pivotal moment in the transformation of Turkey into a modern nation-state.",
